<SECOND>PM-AP Appointment,0110</SECOND>
<HEAD>Correspondent Appointed in Cleveland</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLEVELAND (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kristi Umbreit, correspondent in charge of the
Knoxville, Tenn., bureau of The Associated Press, has been
appointed correspondent in charge at Cleveland.
   Columbus Chief of Bureau Jake Booher announced the appointment
Friday. It is effective June 19.
   Ms. Umbreit, 36, joined the AP in July 1984 as a news clerk in
Louisville, Ky. She became a newswoman in Knoxville in June 1985
and was promoted to Knoxville correspondent in October 1987.
   A native of Minneapolis, she earned a bachelor's degree in
journalism at Memphis State University in 1984. She began her
journalism career with The Memphis Press-Scimitar.
