   King Hassan II is appealing a recent property tax assessment on
his sprawling central California ranch 175 miles northwest of Los
Angeles.
   The monarch owns more than 16,000 acres of ranchland with an
assessed value of nearly $3.7 million. But the king's lawyer said
Thursday the property was only worth about half that much.
   The difference in the tax bill is about $20,000 a year, said
attorney Robin Baggett. He said he believes a compromise can be
reached without a formal appeals hearing.
