<FIRST>r a AM-EyePlucked     06-03 0225</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Eye Plucked,0230</SECOND>
<HEAD>Judge Lifts Jail Term for `Exorcist' Who Plucked Out Boy's Eye</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who plucked out a teen-ager's
eye during an exorcism won't have to go to jail after all, says the
judge who sentenced her last year to a six-month term.
   District Judge Mike McDonald ordered Andrea Cowan, who was
convicted in June 1988 of cruelty to a juvenile, to buy an $850
artificial eye for the boy.
   Mrs. Cowan was pregnant when McDonald sentenced her in October
1988, and he said she would not have to go to jail until after she
gave birth.
   In the meantime, McDonald said Friday, the prosecutor urged him
not to send Mrs. Cowan to jail. She has expressed remorse and her
probation officer describes her as an ideal candidate for
probation, the judge said.
   Mrs. Cowan could have been sentenced to 10 years in prison on
the cruelty charge.
   McDonald said he originally ordered Mrs. Cowan to serve jail
time, as well as doing 300 hours of community service and paying
nearly $4,000 in restitution, to punish her for committing a crime
in the name of Christianity.
   ``In this day of the various scandals which have been widely
publicized, the last thing the Christian cause needs is this type
of additional adverse publicity,'' McDonald said at the time.
</TEXT>
