<SECOND>AM-BRF--Sock Robber,0136</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Robs Restaurant With Sock, Nets $400</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SMYRNA, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bandit made off with $400 from a restaurant
after brandishing a plastic cup and an ice scraper wrapped inside a
white sock, police said.
   The man walked into the Waffle House restaurant in this Atlanta
suburb on Friday and demanded money at, well, sockpoint, Lt. Ed
Clack said. The cashier became nervous and jammed the cash register
as she tried to open it.
   The robber then stepped behind the counter, snatched the
register and bolted out the back door, ``carrying it under his arm
like a football,'' Clack said.
   ``It's not the first robbery we've had with a fake gun,'' he
said. ``It is the first one, though, with an ice scraper, a plastic
cup and a sock.''
