<FIRST>u i AM-Iran-USChronology     06-03 0407</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Iran-US Chronology,0443</SECOND>
<HEAD>Events in Iran-U.S. Relations</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Khomeini</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a chronology of events involving U.S.-Iranian relations:
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1979</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   January _ Shah Mohammad Reza Pahlavi, one of America's
staunchest allies, flees Iran.
   Feb. 1 _ Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini, the Shiite Moslem
patriarch, returns to Tehran after 15 years in exile.
   Nov. 4 _ U.S. Embassy in Tehran stormed by extremists protesting
shah's presence in the United States for medical treatment; 52
hostages taken. U.S. severs ties with Iran.
   Nov. 12 _ President Jimmy Carter stops imports of Iranian oil,
freezes Iranian assets in United States estimated worth $12 billion.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1980</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   April 25 _ U.S. military attempt to rescue hostages fails as
American helicopters crash in Iranian desert storm.
   July 27 _ Shah dies in Egypt after long bout with cancer.
   September _ Iran and Iraq go to war over border dispute.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1981</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   Jan. 20 _ U.S. Embassy hostages freed after 444 days.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1985</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   Midyear _ Washington decides to secretly approve shipments of
U.S. arms to Iran.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1986</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   May 28 _ U.S. National Security Adviser Robert McFarlane makes
secret trip to Iran in attempt to arrange exchange of arms for
American hostages held by pro-Iranian extremists in Lebanon.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1987</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   July _ U.S. Navy units in gulf to escort shipping threatened by
Iran-Iraq war and Kuwait places 11 tankers under U.S. flag for
protection from Iranian attacks in Persian Gulf.
   Sept. 21 _ U.S. helicopters attack Iranian ship Iran Ajr caught
laying mines in central gulf. Four Iranian crewmen killed, 26
wounded and detained, later repatriated via Oman.
   Oct. 8 _ U.S. helicopter gunships sink Iranian speedboat and
disable two others in gulf after U.S. helicopter is fired at.
   Oct. 16 _ A Chinese-made Silkworm missile, fired from the
Iranian-held Faw peninsula, hits the 81,283-ton products carrier
Sea Isle City near Kuwait's oil loading terminal of al-Ahmadi.
Eighteen people wounded including the American master. White House
calls it ``outrageous act of aggression.''
   Oct. 19 _ Four U.S. destroyers shell two oil platforms in Iran's
Rostam oil field in response to the Silkworm attack.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1988</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   July 2 _ USS Vincennes shoots down Iranian jetliner, killing all
290 aboard. Navy says airliner was mistaken for jet fighter.
   Aug. 20 _ United Nations-sponsored cease-fire takes effect in
Iran-Iraq war.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1989</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   February _ Washington denounces Khomeini's death sentence
against British author Salman Rushdie for his book ``The Satanic
Verses.'' Khomeini said the book blasphemed the Islamic faith.
</TEXT>
